.TH "lpfc_issue_reset" 9 "lpfc_issue_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_issue_reset \- Selectively resets an adapter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" lpfc_issue_reset
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
class device that is converted into a Scsi_host.
.IP "attr" 12
device attribute, not used.
.IP "buf" 12
containing the string "selective".
.IP "count" 12
unused variable.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the buf contains the string "selective" then \fBlpfc_selective_reset\fP
is called to perform the reset.
.SH "NOTES"
Assumes any error from \fBlpfc_selective_reset\fP will be negative.
If \fBlpfc_selective_reset\fP returns zero then the length of the buffer
is returned which indicates success
.SH "RETURN"
-EINVAL if the buffer does not contain the string "selective"
length of buf if lpfc-\fBselective_reset\fP if the call succeeds
return value of \fBlpfc_selective_reset\fP if the call fails
